{@--1@} ({%a%}) To stand on or 
upon, to sit in or upon, occupy (as a seat
&c.), resort to; {#arDAsanaM gotraBido'DitazWO#}
<ls>R. 6. 73</ls>; {#SAKinaH kecidaDyazWuH#} <ls>Bk. 15. 31</ls>;
{#pratanubalAnyaDitizWatastapAMsi#} <ls>Ki. 10. 16</ls>
practising; {#mAmaDizWAya#} <ls>Rām.</ls> 
depending on me. ({%b%}) To stand, be;  
{#aDyatizWadaMguzWena SataM samAH#} <ls>Mb.</ls> ({%c%}) To stand
over, mount. ({%d%}) To stand by, be
near; {#ASramabahirvfkzamUlamaDitizWati#} <ls>U. 4.</ls>

{@--2@} To be in, dwell in, inhabit,
reside, stay; {#BujaMgapihitadvAraM#} 
{#pAtAlamaDitizWati#} <ls>R. 1. 80</ls>; {#mADizWA nirjanaM vanaM#}  
<ls>Bk. 8. 79</ls>; {#SrIjayadevaBaRitamaDitizWatu#} 
{#kaMWatawImavirataM#} <ls>Gīt. 11.</ls>

{@--3@} To make
oneself master of, seize, take 
possession of, overpower, conquer; {#saMgrAme#}
{#tAnaDizWAsyan#} <ls>Bk. 9. 72</ls>;  

{#tvamaDizWAsyasi dvizaH#} <ls n="Bk.">16. 40</ls>; {#sa sadA#} 
{#PalaSAlinIM kriyAM SaradaM loka ivADitizWati#}  
<ls>Ki. 2. 31</ls> obtains; {#aDitizWati#} 
{#lokamojasA sa vivasvAniva medinIpatiH#} <ls n="Ki.">2. 38</ls>;
{#yakzaH kutaScidaDizWAya bAlacaMdrikAM nivasati#}
<ls>Dk. 18.</ls>

{@--4@} ({%a%}) To lead, conduct as
head or chief; {#mahArAjadaSaraTasya#} 
{#dArAnaDizWAya vasizWaH prAptaH#} <ls>U. 4</ls>, See {#aDizWita#}
also. ({%b%}) To be at the head of, govern,
direct, preside over, rule, 
superintend; {#prakftiM svAmaDizWAya#} <ls>Bg. 4. 6</ls>
governing, controlling; {#SrotraM cakzuH#} 
{#sparSanaM ca rasanaM GrARameva ca . aDizWAya manaScAyaM#}
{#vizayAnupasevate#} <ls n="Bg.">15. 9</ls> presiding over and
thus turning to use.
